rComments: The man is a special type of pedagogue. He takes an interest in you if you take an interest in yourself. He is always willing to talk during office hours. His material and assessments can best be described as "holistic", but is a refreshing change from the status quo. I think you can learn a lot about the import of philosophy to your life from him.

Doug was really kind and nice in general. I just didn't understand a word he was saying, he mumbles when he talks, like he's talking to himself, and honestly I didn't get a word of it. Dropped the course.

Great class. Prof. Hutchinson is interesting and provides added materials to compliment the texts. If you want to be mentally challenged, then take his course. Marking is fair and the comments are invaluable.

Great class! While Hutchinson seemed to go off topic sometimes, overall his lectures were pretty interesting as he made a lot of connections to what we studied from other sources he brought in. A really nice guy, and is really helpful and considerate to his students. Nice to see a university prof see students as individuals and not numbers.

I'm not even sure what I learned. He discusses his own personal problems and not class material. I advise against taking this course. He makes you read random works from various others, with no particualr point. If this professor is any indication of the PHL department at UofT, then it's a shame.  I feel angry that I paid for this course. HORRIBLE!

DSH is awesome! Really cares about students and willing to help with courses & non-academic stuff. His courses are best for those  genuinely interested in living thoughtfully & learning. Courses require work but are very rewarding. He prefers content over "writing skills". Not for everyone, but amazing for many students, male and female.

Hitchinson is a great professor if you are serious about philosophy (esp. Ancient Philosophy).  He will spend individual time with you if you need help with a topic (although I did take a upper level class with him and not the phl 1st year class).
No Comments

Useless class. I learned nothing execpt about him. Which would be fine I suppose if he was actually a good person, but he is just too self-involved and a completly repugnent indvidual. Avoid his class.
No Comments
He would be a better prof if he gave up the pretensions.
somewhat controversal prof, but only becasue the nerds hate him. awesome proffessor, legendary at u of t

He was the professor who taught me what a university education should be about. He was one of those rare profs who always had an open door policy and most of the times our discussions would go far beyond what the class material was. He was an exceptional teacher, and his classes are very intresting
I think he's a very sincere man, but he would be so much more effective as a teacher without the professorial pretentions.
Would be nice if he wasn't high during lectures.  A major disappointment.

he comes across as self-absorbed when you talk to him one-on-one.  lectures weren't good at teaching the actual material.  mostly just stories about himself.  tries too hard to be eccentric.  irresponsible.

I took several of Prof. Hutchinson's courses about 20 years ago on my way to a PHL degree.  He remains to me an enduring example of what a university professor should be.  Material was difficult, but the brilliance of the man was inspiring.
avoid taking his class unless you already have a solid grasp of the material. no easy marks and difficult to decipher lectures
Great teacher. Wonderfully relaxed manner, and very approachable
The lectures are not all that helpful towards understanding the texts. (Paul Los was more structured in that repsect.) With so much delays and diversions, I think one hour per class is not enough.

WOW, TALK ABOUT NOSTALGIA! I HAD DOUG ALMOST 20 YEARS AGO WHEN HE WAS STILL WORKING ON HIS PHD. HE WAS A NON-CONFORMIST PROF. A LITTLE ECCENTRIC AND RIGID AT TIMES, BUT I CAN'T COMPLAIN, I PASSED BOTH COURSES I TOOK AND I WASN'T EVEN A PHIL. MAJOR.
He is unprofessional - personal information told in confidence should remain confidential.

I can't hear him. Most of the marks are VERY subjective.Don't expect to get high marks. Don't take this course if you are usually a 75% or above student. They give you 85% on one piece of work and then a 50% or a similar one. lecture useless,way off topic

The perfect example of an eccentric but interesting professor. He is not afraid to talk about marijuana, politics and other controversial issues. His teaching style is engaging but his commentary sometimes obscures the meaning of the text.
excellent class format, obviously a lot of work went into course design, may take another phl thanks to this intro.
His brain holds too much info, funny classes--sometimes, not typical
No Comments
Lighten up, you suck.
Intelligent man - but sadly, scattered as well.
funny, eccentric, very smart, interesting and innovative.
